column26: According to transportation planning 200 Jews from Danzig should be connected with this transport. Only 27 of them are known by name.
In this transport there were 158 persons from Norway and 11 from Frankfurt am Main
1342/1285, In addition to the persons from Berlin there were also Jews from Königsberg, Frankfurt am Main, Hannover and Leipzig on this transport.
Therein 18 persons from Leipzig having been taken to Berlin on 18th June 1943.
1196 children and 53 educators from Bialystok and the protectorate Bohemia and Moravia.
Therein also 19 persons from Hamburg having been taken to Berlin on 30th Jan. 1945.
In this transport were inter alia 191 Jews from Frankfurt, 25 from Wiesbaden, 8 from Darmstadt, 18 from the administrative district of Koblenz and 148 Jews from Leipzig.
